                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Book Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">In this eminently readable, concise history of Ethiopia, Harold  Marcus surveys the evolution of the oldest African nation from prehistory to the  present. For the updated edition, Marcus has written a new preface, two new  chapters, and an epilogue, detailing the development and implications of  Ethiopia as a Federal state and the war with Eritrea.  </span>
              
</td></tr></table>
